05659nam a22006615i 9783035610598DE-B159720210824034702.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||210824t20212021sz     fo  d z      eng d  a2021937663  a97830356105987 a10.1515/97830356105982doi  a(DE-B1597)474527  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  aszcCH 7aARC0130002bisacsh00aBreathe :bInvestigations into Our Atmospherically Entangled Future /ced. by Klaus Klaas Loenhart. 1aBasel : bBirkhäuser, c[2021] 4c©2021  a1 online resource (290 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFrontmatter -- tContent -- tIn the Meteorological Turn -- tBeyond Gravity -- tI—The Disappearance of the Outside -- tAir -- tBeing in The Air -- tLiving Within the Air: Towards an Ethics of Breathability -- tA Cultivation of Breathing -- tII—An Atmospheric Consciousness -- tThe Opening of Climate -- tThe Atmospherization of Everyday Experience -- tAtmospheres – New Conditions for Design -- tHow Big is the Atmosphere? -- tIII—Entangling with the World -- tPlant Life: The Political Ecology of Working Together -- tHow Air Creates Atmosphere -- tBecoming-airborne -- tBiometeorological Design – Architectures of the Planetary-Atmospheric Turn -- tAuthors, Acknowledgements0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aDas Buch erkundet das Atmen und die Atmosphäre als Leitmotive für die Gestaltung einer inklusiven Zukunft in einem neuen Klimaregime. Dabei werden die atmosphärischen Verknüpfungen künftiger gesellschaftlicher Aktivitäten aufgespürt. Mit diesem verflochtenen Bewusstsein rücken die performativen Eigenschaften von Luft, Atmosphäre und Klima in den Vordergrund, um sie als maßgebende Akteure für die Konzeption und Gestaltung unseres planetaren Daseins neu zu entdecken. Der sorgfältig editierte Band versammelt namhafte Autoren verschiedener Disziplinen, die mit ihren Ideen, Beobachtungen und Beispielen dazu anregen, unser gesellschaftliches Handeln und Gestalten neu zu denken. Mit Beiträgen von: Bruno Latour Eva Horn, Heather Davis David Life, Bronislaw Szerszynski Jean-Paul Thibaud Gernot Böhme Peter Sloterdijk Rosetta Sarah Elkin Wolfgang Kessling Anja Thierfelder Matthias Schuler Tomás Saraceno Klaus K. Loenhart  aThis book explores breathing and the atmosphere as leitmotifs for the design of an inclusive future in a new climate regime, uncovering intertwinements of societal activities with the air and the atmosphere. With this awareness of entanglement, the deeply performative characteristics of the air, atmosphere and climate are foregrounded and can be discovered as central agents in the conception and design of our planetary existence. This carefully edited collection brings together renowned authors from various disciplines, and their ideas, observations, and examples inspire us to rethink our forms of social action and design. With contributions by: Bruno Latour Eva Horn, Heather Davis David Life, Bronislaw Szerszynski Jean-Paul Thibaud Gernot Böhme Peter Sloterdijk Rosetta Sarah Elkin Wolfgang Kessling Anja Thierfelder Matthias Schuler Tomás Saraceno Klaus K. Loenhart  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 4aArchitekturtheorie. 4aKlimaschutz. 4aLandschaftstheorie. 7aARCHITECTURE / Study & Teaching.2bisacsh1 aBöhme, Gernot, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDavis, Heather, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aElkin, Rosetta Sarah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHorn, Eva, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKessling, Wolfgang, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLatour, Bruno, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1